.TH "batadv_dat_select_candidates" 9 "batadv_dat_select_candidates" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_dat_select_candidates \- select the nodes which the DHT message has to be sent to
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct batadv_dat_candidate *" batadv_dat_select_candidates
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "__be32 ip_dst "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "ip_dst" 12
ipv4 to look up in the DHT
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
An originator O is selected if and only if its DHT_ID value is one of three
closest values (from the LEFT, with wrap around if needed) then the hash
value of the key. ip_dst is the key.
.SH "RETURN"
the candidate array of size BATADV_DAT_CANDIDATE_NUM.
